stanford's entrepreneurship corner judith grunert anker pub co entrepreneurship corner logo stanford technology ventures program logo about blog sponsors popular videos podcasts speakers browse subscribe login email password remember me register judith grunert anker pub co judy works with syracuse university department and program faculty department chairs and college deans to improve student learning through course and curriculum design and program evaluation her interests center on the ways that faculty can help students become the agents of their own learning and she published the course syllabus a learning centered approach and a recent chapter course design for large classes for m erin porter and christine a stanley's book engaging large classes to support faculty in their efforts she has coordinated and contributed to the design and development of national projects for higher education for government and not for profit organizations a former member of the syracuse university faculty in the college of visual and performing arts she joined the center in 1995 and is currently completing doctoral studies instructional design development & evaluation related links cstl syr edu last updated sat may 21 2005 displaying one result found for judith grunert page 1 category title author speaker organization length date book the course syllabus a learning centered approach this best selling practical manual presents why and how to construct a syllabus that shifts from what you will cover the traditional syllabus to one that reflects what tools and information you can provide students to help them learn the learning centered syllabus the book's underlying assumption is that good teaching helps students understand how to actively acquire use and extend knowledge in an ongoing process of learning the book's goal is to assist anyone interested in designing a learning centered syllabus to plan and construct one from amazon judith grunert anker pub co 97 pages 01 2000 latest vid